.TH "uclogic_params_pen_init_v2" 9 "uclogic_params_pen_init_v2" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uclogic_params_pen_init_v2 \- initialize tablet interface pen input and retrieve its parameters from the device, using v2 protocol.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" uclogic_params_pen_init_v2
.BI "(struct uclogic_params_pen *pen "  ","
.BI "bool *pfound "  ","
.BI "struct hid_device *hdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pen" 12
Pointer to the pen parameters to initialize (to be
cleaned up with \fBuclogic_params_pen_cleanup\fP). Not modified in
case of error, or if parameters are not found. Cannot be NULL.
.IP "pfound" 12
Location for a flag which is set to true if the parameters
were found, and to false if not (e.g. device was
incompatible). Not modified in case of error. Cannot be NULL.
.IP "hdev" 12
The HID device of the tablet interface to initialize and get
parameters from. Cannot be NULL.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero, if successful. A negative errno code on error.
